      "url": "https://cdn.misoenergy.org/20240304%20Queue%20Process%20Workshop%20Presentation632005.pdf",
      "title": "Queue Process Workshop Generator Interconnection Queue",
      "text": "March 4, 2024\n\n##### Queue ProcessWorkshop\n\nGenerator Interconnection Queue\n\nWelcome\n\n1\n\nThis is an overview of MISO’s Generation InterconnectionQueue (GIQ) processes. The following slides present an overview ofthe purpose, objectives, concepts, and planning related to GIQ.\n\n2\n\nThis presentation is intended for those individuals seeking an understanding of MISO’s GIQ – including the associated processes. This presentation is being recorded and will be posted to the MISO Learning Center.\n\n3\n\nPrevious training presentations on MISOPlanning are at respectively higher levels. Those presentations focus on the broader concepts and processes.\n\n4\n\nFrequently used terminology, along with reference-links to MISO documentation and contacts, are included in this presentation.\n\nDisclaimer: The following materials have been developed for use as training materials only. These materials do not, and are not intended to support, govern or affect in any way market activities other than for training for which these materials were developed. Those seeking governance or business practice guidance are urged to consult relevant sections in the MISO Tariff and Business Practice Manuals available through the MISO website. Any data used in these materials or in training scenarios is test data developed solely for use in a test environment for training purposes. None of this data should be relied upon for any purpose other than the training for which it was developed.\n\nAgenda\n\n• Pre-Queue, Application Submission & Application Review\n\n• GI Finance • Site Control • Application Best Practices • Definitive Planning Phase (DPP)\n\n• GI Online Application Tool Overview • Questions & Answers • Helpful Resources • Adjournment\n\nGoHome\n\nIntroduction\n\nQueue Process Training Workshop • 3/4/2024\n\nApplication Window Opens • 3/18/2024 @ 9am ET\n\nApplication Deadline\n\n• 4/18/2024 @ 5pm ET \n• All applications, payments, site control, etc. must be submitted \n\nDPP-2023-Cycle Application Window\n\nTraining\n\n• It is highly recommended for stakeholders to review the online training available on the MISO Learning Center. The online training was created to help applicants and TOs navigate the GI Portal. These guides are posted to the MISO Customer Learning Center under Transmission & Generation Planning and Resource Adequacy. \n• Refer to the Workshop section on the MISO public website for previous workshop presentations. \n\nGoHome\n\nGenerator Interconnection Process\n\nGoHome\n\n### Pre-Queue\n\nGoHome\n\nOverview ofthe Pre Queue Phase\n\nNote: Ad-Hoc Meeting Requests received after 5:00 pm ET on March 8, 2024 will be scheduled after the April 18, 2024 deadline.\n\nOverview of the Pre-Queue Phase\n\n| | | | | |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| | | | | Overview of POI self-check Purpose: tool |\n| | | | Key | Takeaways: |\n| | | | • POI Interconnection potential • The | self-check tool is designed to help Customers pre-screen for POIs results are for information and do only |\n| 9 | POI - Point of POI Tool Workshop (Demonstration) Please reference the MISO | Interconnection LMS at https://miso.csod.com/ | not | include voltage or constraints stability for more extensive training on the MISO DPP process |\n\nSelect an Area on the Map\n\nPlease reference the MISO LMS at https://miso.csod.com/ for more extensive training on the MISO DPP process 10\n\n4 GoHome\n\n### Application Submission\n\nGoHome\n\nOverview Application Submission & Review Process ofthe Pre Queue Phase\n\nGoHome\n\n• Definitive gross and net generator output(MW)as measuredatthe POI \n• Definitive POI- Only 1 POI may enter into the DPP unless requiredby State regulations to take 2 POIs \n• Definitive one-line diagram for the POI – Information shall include: \n• Breaker layout, bus configuration (if available) and numberof generators \n• The zero-sequence impedance (if applicable) \n• The distance fromthe collector substation to the POI referencedin miles and the line impedance \n• Ifthe POI is a line tap, distance fromthe tap to the endpoints ofthe existing line referencedin miles \n• Generator step up (GSU)transformerdata and collector substation transformerdate (if applicable) \n• For inverter-based generators,FERC Order827 requires \n• Location and size of any dynamic and/or staticVAR compensation devises \n• Equivalent collector systemimpedance \n• Power flow models required \n• All generatorTypes: Generic Standard Library Stability Model representing the dynamics ofthe Generating Facility in .dyr format, models submitted must be acceptable and not found in Appendix A: NERC Unacceptable Model List posted at https://www.nerc.com/pa/RAPA/ModelAssessment/Documents/Dynamic%20Modeling%20Recommendations.pdf and also comply with MISO’s Model Data requirements and Reporting Procedures posted at https://www.misoenergy.org/planning/planning-modeling/. FERC Order842 requiresnewly interconnecting units to install, maintain and operate equipment capable of providing primary frequency response as a condition of interconnection,the order requires ICs to provide a plant controller for inverter-based generationor governor modelfor thermalunits in the provided dynamics model \n• For inverter based/non-synchronous generators, FERC Order 827 requires \n• Demonstration thatthe plant can meet a PF of 0.95 lead/lag atthe high side on the main GSUs (TheTOs planning criteria will supersede ifthey require a morestringentPF) \n• Baseturbine or inverter reactive capability (inherentpower factor) \n• For inverter based (wind or solar) generators,the ICshall provide the short circuit modeling instruction manual and associated model data \n• All GeneratorTypes: All applicable informationrequested in Attachment A or Appendix 1 \n\nDuring the Application Process, any changes requirea submissionofthe correcteddocuments.\n\nTechnical Requirements\n\nGoHome\n\n• Include breakdown of installed capacity for hybrid applications in comments section \n• Include POI bus numbers in application \n• Utilize a standard 2% loss calculation for installed capacity \n• The final COD year of the study used for DPP-2023 projects it 2028. The modeling only goes out to 2028 per engineering (for DPP 2023 projects). \n• Please do not reuse Project Common names \n\nTechnical Requirements (Cont'd)\n\nGoHome\n\n### Application Review\n\nGoHome\n\n…Application Review\n\nGoHome\n\nOverview Deficiency Requirements ofthe Pre Queue Phase\n\n• Upon submittal of an application and deposit, MISO will conduct the application review within 15 business days\n\n• MISO will notify the customer of any deficiencies, triggering a 10 business day corrections period\n\n• All deficiencies must be cured within the first corrections period. No additional time will be provided\n\nApplication Submittal\n\nNo later than April 18, 2024 @5pm ET\n\nMISO Reviews\n\n15 Business Days\n\nCustomer Corrections\n\n10 Business Days\n\nGoHome\n\n### GI Finance\n\nGoHome\n\nOverview Banking Information ofthe Pre Queue Phase\n\nPayment in full is recommended at time of Application Submission. \nAll payments must be submitted in full before a J number is assigned. \n\nMilestone Payment Requirements\n\n• Each payment must be submitted separately; DO NOT COMBINE PAYMENTS \n• D1 – ACH/Wire Payment Only \n• D2 – ACH/Wire Payment Only \n• M2 – ACH/Wire Payment or Irrevocable Letter of Credit \n• Reference the Application ID # in the memo of each ACH/Wire payment \n• Contact gifinance@misoenergy.org for wiring instructions \n• Use the MISO GI – Exhibit II – Letter of Credit Template if choosing this option; it too must include the Application ID # \n• Review the GI – Exhibit II – Letter of Credit FAQ for additional information \n• Upload Letter of Credit to the Application in the applicable area \n• Mail original Letter of Credit to MISO via Overnight/Standard or Certified Mail. The mailing address is listed on the FAQ. \n\nGoHome\n\nOverview Banking Information Continued ofthe Pre Queue Phase\n\nState or Federal Tax Form Requirements\n\n• W-9 Form: An Internal Revenue Service Form W-9 or comparable state issued document for the Interconnection Customer submittin",
