      "text": "GIA Small Generator Insurance Requirements 5 MW and Under\n\nSkip to main content Skip to footer\n\n# MISO Dashboard\n\n#### Last Modified - 03/19/2026\n\n## GIA Small Generator Insurance Requirements 5 MW and Under PAC-2025-1\n\nLegend\n\nE\n\nD\n\nD\n\nFERC\n\nI\n\n| 2025 | 2026 |\n| --- | --- |\n| Q1 | Q2 | Q3 | Q4 | Q1 | Q2 | Q3 | Q4 |\n\n#### Overview\n\n##### Phase\n\nI\n\n##### Entities\n\nActive: Interconnection Process Working Group (IPWG)\n\n##### Next Update\n\nQuarter 4, 2025\n\n##### Origin\n\n##### Status\n\nActive\n\n##### MISO Initiatives\n\n#### Quick Link\n\nDistributed generation projects present unique factual circumstances that make it uneconomical to execute MISO’s pro forma GIA, thereby necessitating approval of changes to Section 18.4.4 of MISO’s pro forma GIA - to reduce insurance requirements in LGIA for small generators 5 MW and under that are Fast Track eligible. MISO should add language to the proforma GIA to require projects 5 mw and under that are eligible under the Fast Track rules to carry excess public liability insurance with a minimum limit of $5 million per occurrence/$5 million aggregate.\n\n### Updates\n\nSorry, no results were found that match your query.\n\n### Issue Materials\n\n#### Documents/Whitepapers\n\n#### FERC Filings and Orders",
